  "text": "The Chromium multi-process architecture is defined across several key files:\n\n1. **RenderProcessHostImpl** (content/browser/renderer_host/render_process_host_impl.h, line 195): This class represents the browser-side representation of a renderer process. It implements the RenderProcessHost interface and manages communication with the renderer process through IPC and Mojo.\n\n2. **BrowserMainLoop** (content/browser/browser_main_loop.h, line 106): This class implements the main browser process event loop, handling initialization, message loop creation, and startup task management.\n\n3. **RenderThreadImpl** (content/renderer/render_thread_impl.h, line 126): This class represents the main thread of a renderer process, where blink::WebView instances live. It handles both Mojo and legacy IPC messages routed by rendering frame IDs.\n\n4. **ChildProcessLauncher** (content/browser/child_process_launcher.h, line 212): This class is responsible for asynchronously spawning child processes (renderer, GPU, utility, etc.). It handles the process creation, notification of launch completion/failure, and process lifecycle management.\n\n5. **content.mojom.Renderer** interface (content/common/renderer.mojom, line 49): This is the primordial Channel-associated Mojo interface implemented by render processes. It defines the browser-to-renderer control messages including CreateAgentSchedulingGroup, CreateAssociatedAgentSchedulingGroup, and other process-level initialization methods.\n\nThese components work together to establish and maintain the multi-process architecture where the browser process (containing BrowserMainLoop) manages renderer processes (represented by RenderProcessHostImpl) through ChildProcessLauncher, with communication occurring via the Renderer Mojo interface."
}

